{
  "text": "The axial and coronal T2 maps without fat saturation were obtained through the pelvic girdle using a T2- weighted multislice, multiecho sequence to quantify the spatial distribution of the T2 relaxation times. A nine echo train length was utilized: TE = 9, 18,\u2026, 99 msec, TR = 1,500 msec. The acquisition time for each T2 map was approximately 3.5 minutes. The total imaging time for both the conventional MRI and the T2 mapping sequences ranged from 45 to 60 minutes. No intravenous contrast or sedation was utilized. As the T2 values can be affected by exercise or activity [CITATION_1] , the patients were requested to not excessively ambulate or exercise for the 12 hours prior to the MRI evaluations.",
